		<div id="sleipnir">
			<h3><span>Sleipnir - What's That?</span></h3>
			<p class="p1"><span>Odin is the name of the software which provides the central repository and its features.</span></p>
			<p class="p2"><span>Sleipnir is the name of the software which you can use to work with the Odin repository.</span></p>
		</div>

		<div id="names">
			<h3><span>Why The Names?</span></h3>
			<p class="p1"><span>Odin is the name of the chief god in Norse mythology who is often associated with knowledge and wisdom. The acronym was built around this initial name: Odin.</span></p>
			<p class="p2"><span>Sleipnir is Odin's mythical eight-legged horse. Here, instead of transporting Odin on horse-back, Sleipnir is performing the function of transporting data to and from your desktop and the Odin servers.</span></p>
		</div>
